Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, fry the @Diced British Chicken Breast{240%grams} and @Sliced Mushrooms{80%grams}, ~{6-8%mins}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. 

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat.

Meanwhile, pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Boil the @Jasmine Rice{150%grams}, ~{12-13%mins}.

Once cooked, drain, pop back in the pan and cover.

Add the @Coleslaw Mix{120%grams} to the chicken.

Stir-fry, ~{2-3%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Cook so there's no pink in the middle of the chicken.

Stir in the @Gochujang Paste{60%grams}, @Bulgogi Sauce{100%grams} and @Water for the Sauce{50%ml}. Simmer, ~{1-2%mins}.

Share the rice between your #bowls{}.

Taste and season the chicken with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Spoon over the rice.

Sprinkle over the @Roasted White Sesame Seeds{5%grams}.

Enjoy!